> Guo Shiyuan is a research assistant in  <a style='color: black;' href='http://medicine.nus.edu.sg/ant/'>Department of Anatomy, Yong Loo Lin School of Medicine, NUS</a>. His research focuses on elucidating breast cancer pathogenesis and discovering novel molecule pathways in improving clinical outcomes. He is interested in approching oncology questions with a data-driven approach. He is also interested literate programming by integrating R/ess and Emacs orgmode in a workflow. 

> In his spare time, he is a member of Aquathlon Team, NUS. 

